                     /note="phiC31 bacterial attachment site attB, the 34 bp
                     natural target in the Streptomyces coelicolor chromosome
                     recognized by the phiC31 large serine integrase
                     (unidirectional; no host cofactors; cannot excise without
                     an RDF). Central TT crossover dinucleotide; attB and attP
                     share only a very short central core (~39% overall
                     identity), the basis of the reaction directionality. In
                     non-native hosts (human/other) phiC31 Int also recombines
                     with degenerate genomic pseudo-attP sites; there is no
                     single canonical pseudo-attB. Cognate phage site:
                     phiC31_attP."
